The paper deals with unsupervised clustering in noisy datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The use of wavelet transforms and the proposed adaptive clustering algorithm suggest a focus on machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DM). The mention of natural datasets and the use of grid labeling data structure suggest a possible focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). The mention of linear time and no pre-knowledge on data models suggest a possible focus on information theory (cs.IT).
